Responsibilities

Overseeing, coordinating and taking the lead role in providing compliance and market risk advice and support to the investment teams on various day to day matters;
Developing and maintaining various programs to ensure adherence to investment mandate and risk control policies;
Ensure achievement of all requirements for risk and compliance reporting and escalation of risks as required;
Ensure adherence to risk management frameworks through effective implementation of a consistent enterprise risk and control management regime across the company;
Building strong relationships with portfolio managers to have risk discussions and facilitate risk management framework implementation including:- promoting awareness of risk and risk management best practices, and as needed, working with and advising portfolio managers in developing effective mitigation steps and controls, analyzing and reporting firm level risk themes, risk levels and focus action items.

Requirement

Master or above with good school/academic records;
Working experience in financial industry would be an advantage;
A good team player with good communication and interpersonal skill;
Strong analytical minds with solid execution skills;
Excellent command of written and spoken English and Putonghua;
Possess of programing skills of at least one of following: SQL, Python, R, C, C#;
Fresh graduate will also be considered.

We offer an attractive remuneration with excellent opportunities to the right candidate. Interested parties please apply with detailed resume. (All personal information received will be kept in strictly confidential and only for recruitment purpose only.)

Job description: An excellent legal and compliance opportunity in a global asset management firm.


Requirements:

We’re looking for a mature and independent team-player. The ideal candidate should:
have degree or higher diploma majoring in law or related discipline;
have about 10-15 years’ experience gained in the field of financial laws, asset management, corporate administration or related financial services;
be proficient in English and Chinese;
possess strong analytical and communication skills;
well-organised and is able to multi-tasks at the same time; and
be proactive and a good team-player.
Applicant with less experience may also be considered.



Job duties:

Assist in the creation and maintenance of investment funds documentation database;
Work closely with back office, front office and service providers on corporate administration and compliance matters;
Work closely with compliance consultants to support the SFC licensing, continuous professional training monitoring and other compliance process;
Assist in the preparation of basic corporate and/or legal documents (e.g. board resolutions);
Assist in the implementation of compliance policies and controls applicable to the Group;
Provide administrative support to the team;
Handle ad hoc projects and duties.



Interested candidates please send full resume with expected salary by clicking "Apply Now".

Personal data provided by job applicants will be used for recruitment purposes only and will be treated in strict confidential.

The Company
Our client is Chinese based private equity company. They are looking for a junior Fund Accountant Associate to join the team.

The Role

Preparing and review financial statements of SPVs;
Providing day-to-day fund accounting;
Preparing of Management Accountants and Financial Statements;
Reviewing monthly NAV calculation;
Assisting asset management team with compilation and analysis for investment budgets and business plans;
Completing portfolio and client analysis;
Assisting to provide KYC documents for bank opening purpose;
Acting as liaison support between asset management, joint venture partners, and fund clients ;
Reviewing capital call and distribution calculations prepared by subordinates.

Your Profile


Good interpersonal skills and ability to cooperate
Good analytical and problem solving skills
Able to work under pressure in meeting deadlines
At least 4+ years of experience in asset management / buy-side companies / big 4
Degree holding in Accounting, Finance or Economics
Qualification in HKICPA/ACCA or similar qualifications are highly preferred

Apply Today
To apply online (Word attachment only), please click the 'Apply' button. Interested parties please apply with the most updated CV with expected salary and available date via JobsDB. Applicants who do not hear from us within 2 weeks may consider their applications unsuccessful. 

About Pathos
We are Pathos Consultancy Limited, a boutique recruitment firm based in Hong Kong strategically placing our candidates across all levels in permanent, temporary and contract roles.  We specialize in IT and finance roles for banking, financial services and listed MNC sectors.

Job Description

Act as a Responsible Officer to supervise Type 1, 4 & 9 regulated activities in compliance with SFC regulations, including fund management;
Assist in SFC license RA1 application; 
Provide advice and support to management on strategic activities and daily operations;
Prepare materials and present for Investment Committee meeting;
Develop and maintain compliance manual and corresponding workflows to ensure compliance with internal policies and external legislation and regulations.; and
Perform other ad-hoc projects and assignments as required.

Requirements



Sound knowledge of SFO, regulations and guidelines of relevant regulatory authorities and risk management control;
Degree holder in Finance, Economics or a business-related discipline;
Licensed SFC Responsible Officer for Type 1, 4 & 9 regulated activities (without conditions);
Experience in application of SFC licensing;
Minimum 3-year relevant experience as a Responsible Officer in Type 1, 4 & 9 regulated activities including at least 1 year of Type 1 and Type 9 experience; and
Good command of written & spoken English and Chinese, proficiency in Mandarin Chinese is preferred.
Please state your current and expected salary in your CV.

Responsibilities:

• To support institutional sales coverage for all fixed income products;

• To facilitate client on-boarding for existing and prospective institutional clients;

• To support new business development and new product roll-out;

• To support marketing efforts such organizing and participating in conferences, corporate access events etc;

• To carry out other duties which may be given by the Supervisor, in which such assignments are consistent with the scope of employment. 

Requirements:

• A Bachelor's degree and qualified to be a licensed person under SFC;

• 3-5 year of sales-related work experience;

• Strong interpersonal and presentation skills;

• Highly independent and strong problem-solving ability;

• Language skills required include Mandarin and English. Proficiency in Cantonese will be a plus.

Responsibilities:

Verify clients' account opening/AML documents to proceed account opening process and handle clients’ enquiries;
Assist trade execution and settlement for mutual funds;
Provide administrative support including data input, document filing and generate reports from computing system;
Prepare client/transactions reports and conduct periodical reviews to meet regulatory requirements;
Perform other ad-hoc projects such as system enhancement, user acceptance testing, etc.

Requirements:

2 years or above in relevant experience, preferably in asset management
Knowledgeable on mutual fund operations preferably
Eligible for SFC Type 1 representative license 
Good command in English, Cantonese and Mandarin
Good communication skill and proficiency in MS Office
Immediate available is preferred

Responsibilities

Handle all general accounting and office administrative works;
Prepare monthly and annual financial and management reports for the management and audit purpose;
Monitoring cash flow and assist in budgeting;
Assist in HR & Co Secretary affairs
Handle any ad hoc projects assigned by the management
Requirements

Degree holder in Finance, Accounting / Qualification of LCC higher or above
3+ years' experience in handling the full sets of accounting
Knowledge in using MYOB accounting software preferably;
With strong sense of responsibility and able to meet tight deadline with high accuracy;
Ability to handle ad-hoc requests;
Proficiency PC skills in Microsoft Word and Excel;
Fluent in Mandarin and good command of English;
Immediate availability is advantage;

Scope of Responsibilities:


Responsible for fund operations, including managing board meeting minutes, investor notices, payment applications, KYC and bank account maintenance;
Manage internal and external key stakeholders; fund administrators, nominee agents, legal counsel and compliance and other related parties;
Coordinate work with product managers, fund managers, legal consultants, accountants and other relevant units;
Responsible to perform fund operations / accounting and administrative works related to all funds
Ad hoc tasks as required.

Skills & Qualifications:


Degree holder in BBA or related areas;
1 year experience in Investment Management, Fund Operations, Accounting or Banking;
Exposure in operations and all rounded middle-to-back office support duties is preferred;
Good command of the use of Excel, Word, PowerPoint and operation systems;
Excellent verbal and written communication skills – Mandarin and English;
Team player and strong ability to multi-tasks;
Independent, attentive to details, self-motivated, keen to learn, ability to adapt new challenges/changes;

We offer:

Competitive package + year-end bonus + insurance benefit
Full range of professional training program
Bright career path to every successful candidate
Company sponsors selected professional qualification

If you are ready to challenge yourself in a performance-driven and dynamic culture that recognizes and rewards talent, we would like to meet you. We are an equal opportunity employer. Our application process is completely secure and confidential. When you submit your credentials, we will review your application, examine your qualifications. We will contact you to pursue a conversation if your background and skills align with our firm’s needs.

***Please provide your current and expected salary, thank you.

Fund Operation Associate

A top performing fund manager (AUM 1bn USD +) is looking for a Junior Fund Operation expert to expand their business in Hong Kong. This candidate is expected to be fluent in Mandarin & English and have solid Fund Accounting experience in Hedge Funds, Private Equity, Asset Managements or Fund Admins

We are looking for young & high calibers candidate to join our professional team.

Responsibilities

Responsible for the oversight of fund operation;

Handle trade booking, settlement, NAV review & reconciliation;

Liaise with fund administrators, brokers, custodians, auditors on various fund operations task; Provide support to different parties;

Handle investors’ subscriptions/redemptions and address related enquires;

Responsible for regulatory reporting;

Ensure adherence to compliance & regulation, review & enhancement on internal control, etc.

Update marketing materials and other investors' related reports;

Provide supports and ad hoc tasks which assigned in the team.

Requirements

University graduates in business related disciplines;

Minimum 1 years of Operation experience; both buy side or sell side is welcome; Experiences in audit firm is preferred.

Experience in hedge fund operation & EQ & series accounting is a must;

Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese and Mandarin;

Outstanding negotiation, planning, analytical, problem solving and decision-making skills.

Job Purpose

Reporting to a Private Equity Director, the candidate is taking a major execution role from preparing pitchbook to deal execution.

Key Responsibilities

Preparing company pitchbooks in Chinese and English;
Conducting research in health care / technology / blockchain related sectors, providing insights and generating investment views;
Work independently in carrying out investment analysis and investment report to the investment target through investigating the financial reports and market information, etc;
Building financial models and valuation analysis of the target investment;
Participating in due diligence for active deals and possible portfolio company monitoring in the after-investment stage.

Requirements

Bachelor's degree or above, with major in Economics, Finance, Accounting, Business Administration or related discipline(s); CPA or CFA is a plus;
2-3 years of working experience in Private Equity and related investment nature;
Well versed in DCF modelling, corporate valuations and due diligence;
Understanding the whole process of running a PE fund from deal sourcing to deal execution;
Highly skilled in using MS Office especially power point to make pitchbook presentation in Chinese and English;
Good writing, analytical and quantitative skills;
Self-motivated, independent and pleasant personality with good communication skills
Good command of written and spoken English and Chinese (including Putonghua)

Responsibilities


Coordinate and involve in activities and events with external business partners
To conduct related research and presentation
To prepare marketing materials where necessary
To support operations of business
Formulate strategic development planning to management
To assist in any ad hoc assignments

 Requirements

         Bachelor’s degree holder in relevant disciplines;
         At least 2-3 years relevant experience in financial institutions;
         Sound knowledge of the financial markets, investment products;
         Commercial savvy on family office market trends;
         Analytical-thinking and outgoing;
         Willing to work as part of a team, where interdependencies and communication across external parties will be common and ongoing;
         Excellent command of spoken and written Chinese and English (including Mandarin)
